WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:10.834
Kneel.

3
00:04:15.464 --> 00:04:17.507
I can make it clean. or...

4
00:04:17.591 --> 00:04:19.676
Might I at least know
the accusation. my prince?

5
00:04:19.760 --> 00:04:21.052
Where is he?

6
00:04:21.845 --> 00:04:23.638
- Who?
- My brother. the king.

7
00:04:23.722 --> 00:04:24.931
In his quarters!

8
00:04:26.099 --> 00:04:28.351
You are a traitor to the crown.

9
00:04:28.435 --> 00:04:30.061
- I sentence you to die.
- No!

10
00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:31.688
My prince.

11
00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:35.776
It appears Lord Larys
has fled the Keep as well.

12
00:04:50.916 --> 00:04:53.043
I need milk of the poppy.

13
00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:56.046
I'm afraid in our hasty flight
that I neglected to bring any.

14
00:04:56.129 --> 00:04:57.839
The pain!

15
00:04:57.923 --> 00:05:00.217
Please. Please.

16
00:05:01.927 --> 00:05:03.220
Take heart. my king.

17
00:05:04.387 --> 00:05:05.931
These are dark hours. but...

18
00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:08.975
brighter days lie ahead.

19
00:05:09.059 --> 00:05:11.353
No. No.

20
00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:14.731
I'm the king of nothing.

21
00:05:15.982 --> 00:05:20.153
With raven shit for a throne
and a cripple for a protector.

22
00:05:21.238 --> 00:05:23.240
I'm fucking pathetic.

23
00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:28.495
Fuck!

24
00:05:32.957 --> 00:05:34.376
Draw your hood.

25
00:05:52.310 --> 00:05:53.687
Wait. no. wait!

26
00:05:59.693 --> 00:06:01.236
Who are you?

27
00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:03.238
Simple men in service of the Citadel.

28
00:06:05.115 --> 00:06:07.158
We're taking these ravens to White Harbor.

29
00:06:07.242 --> 00:06:09.244
You're in the queen's lands.

30
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:13.415
If you mean to pass.
you first have to denounce the usurper.

31
00:06:13.498 --> 00:06:15.041
bend the knee.

32
00:06:15.125 --> 00:06:20.881
You swear fealty to Her Grace.
the one true queen. Rhaenyra Targaryen.

33
00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:27.512
We denounce the usurper

34
00:06:27.596 --> 00:06:30.640
and swear to Her Grace.
Rhaenyra Targaryen.

35
00:06:36.646 --> 00:06:37.646
Come on. friend.

36
00:06:38.148 --> 00:06:40.317
Affirm your fealty
so we might be on our way.

37
00:06:44.905 --> 00:06:46.531
The captain said kneel.

38
00:06:46.615 --> 00:06:47.949
Fuck you.

39
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:56.179
Forgive my friend. he can be so stubborn.

40
00:06:56.832 --> 00:06:58.043
They're for Aegon.

41
00:06:58.877 --> 00:07:00.670
Put them to the sword.

42
00:07:00.754 --> 00:07:03.314
- Wait. please. Please.
- It's a very lucky day for you. my lord.

43
00:07:05.133 --> 00:07:08.970
The reason this man won't swear
fealty to Rhaenyra...

44
00:07:11.681 --> 00:07:13.725
is because he is Aegon Targaryen.

45
00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:17.103
What?

46
00:07:17.604 --> 00:07:19.856
No. no. that's...

47
00:07:19.940 --> 00:07:22.734
What are you playing at. friend?
Always jesting.

48
00:07:22.817 --> 00:07:24.611
- That true?
- No.

49
00:07:24.694 --> 00:07:27.322
No. of course not. These are lies.

50
00:07:27.405 --> 00:07:29.699
He was lustrated in dragon fire
by Rhaenys Targaryen...

51
00:07:29.783 --> 00:07:30.659
- No.
- And her dragon

52
00:07:30.742 --> 00:07:31.844
at the Battle of Rook's Rest.

53
00:07:31.868 --> 00:07:33.620
My companion is always the gifted mummer.

54
00:07:33.703 --> 00:07:36.098
- I am His Grace's loyal councillor...
- Always making grand claims

55
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:37.391
- for his entertainment.
- And the Lord of Harrenhal...

56
00:07:37.415 --> 00:07:39.084
Outrageous fucking lies!

57
00:07:39.167 --> 00:07:40.293
Someone's lying.

58
00:07:40.377 --> 00:07:42.003
- His crown.
- No.

59
00:08:01.815 --> 00:08:03.358
Pretty hair.

60
00:08:05.652 --> 00:08:06.987
Take their heads.

61
00:08:07.946 --> 00:08:09.948
We'll make a rich bounty for the queen.

62
00:08:10.031 --> 00:08:11.217
- Forgive me. my lord...
- No. no. no. please.

63
00:08:11.241 --> 00:08:13.401
But you would lose
your own head for such a misstep.

64
00:08:14.744 --> 00:08:16.621
This is the challenger himself.

65
00:08:18.707 --> 00:08:20.875
You can name your price
for delivering him...

66
00:08:21.876 --> 00:08:27.257
and his most trusted confidant
to the queen as living hostages.

67
00:08:29.467 --> 00:08:30.969
Who are they. then?

68
00:08:31.052 --> 00:08:32.636
No one of consequence.

69
00:08:36.307 --> 00:08:37.475
What's the nearest port?

70
00:08:37.558 --> 00:08:38.768
Duskendale.

71
00:08:40.102 --> 00:08:41.145
Bar them within.

72
00:08:41.229 --> 00:08:42.522
We'll take them there.

73
00:08:43.982 --> 00:08:45.734
And hire a ship to Dragonstone.

74
00:08:48.611 --> 00:08:50.363
I have to believe...

75
00:08:51.990 --> 00:08:54.159
that Alicent's offer was genuine.

76
00:08:55.452 --> 00:08:58.830
It is a ruse cloaked in stale friendship.

77
00:08:58.913 --> 00:09:01.541
The risk she took in coming here
is beyond question.

78
00:09:02.667 --> 00:09:04.502
And the risk she now asks you to take?

79
00:09:07.464 --> 00:09:12.260
To fly to the Greens' stronghold
based on her word alone.

80
00:09:14.679 --> 00:09:16.514
It is a trap. Mother...

81
00:09:17.599 --> 00:09:20.977
to lure you and Daemon into Vhagar's jaws.

82
00:09:21.061 --> 00:09:25.065
No! Vhagar and Aemond are gone.
They have flown to Harrenhal.

83
00:09:25.148 --> 00:09:28.693
And Aegon is bedridden.

84
00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:40.288
I could take both Aegon and the throne

85
00:09:40.371 --> 00:09:41.998
in a single stroke.

86
00:09:42.082 --> 00:09:43.083
No.

87
00:09:44.125 --> 00:09:46.044
You cannot trust her.

88
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:49.631
Mother.

89
00:09:52.550 --> 00:09:54.302
Alicent came to Dragonstone.

90
00:09:54.385 --> 00:09:57.388
- Alicent?
- Under a banner of peace.

91
00:09:57.472 --> 00:09:58.681
Surely. this is not possible.

92
00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:01.434
The Greens know already
that their defeat is written.

93
00:10:04.062 --> 00:10:08.608
Aemond flies on Vhagar
to join Cole in the Riverlands.

94
00:10:09.567 --> 00:10:13.404
With him gone. Alicent will open
the gates of the Red Keep

95
00:10:13.488 --> 00:10:15.824
and surrender Aegon to me.

96
00:10:15.907 --> 00:10:18.368
I will then take his head and the throne.

97
00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:20.453
What are her terms. Your Grace?

98
00:10:20.537 --> 00:10:22.914
That she. Helaena.
and Jaehaera are spared.

99
00:10:22.997 --> 00:10:25.542
and that this war ends
without further bloodshed.

100
00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:28.670
That is a low price.
Do you believe she can be trusted?

101
00:10:28.753 --> 00:10:30.755
Get word to Lord Corlys in the Gullet.

102
00:10:30.839 --> 00:10:33.800
I require ships to deliver
fighting men enough to secure the city.

103
00:10:33.883 --> 00:10:35.885
Your Grace. I protest
this action with all my po...

104
00:10:35.969 --> 00:10:37.196
And Daemon must return with haste.

105
00:10:37.220 --> 00:10:38.596
I'll write to him.

106
00:10:39.806 --> 00:10:42.267
We'll fly to King's Landing
in two days' time...

107
00:10:43.351 --> 00:10:45.186
and take the city.

108
00:10:55.905 --> 00:10:58.366
Good morrow. ser. My queen.

109
00:10:58.992 --> 00:11:00.192
The king requires an audience.

110
00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:19.179
Rather to the throne room. Your Grace.

111
00:11:33.651 --> 00:11:34.652
Aemond.

112
00:11:40.992 --> 00:11:42.410
Why are you here?

113
00:11:49.792 --> 00:11:51.419
Aegon has abdicated the throne.

114
00:11:53.880 --> 00:11:55.173
Abdicated? What do you mean?

115
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:58.468
Fled King's Landing with that toad Larys.

116
00:11:59.886 --> 00:12:02.513
No. Aegon was bedridden.

117
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:05.266
Where could he have gone? Why?

118
00:12:05.350 --> 00:12:07.560
Because he's even more stupid
than he is craven.

119
00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:11.418
We must send a search party.
He needs to be found immediately.

120
00:12:11.648 --> 00:12:13.608
Where were you. Mother?

121
00:12:15.235 --> 00:12:17.445
You've not been seen in the Keep in days.

122
00:12:25.912 --> 00:12:27.664
I was in the Kingswood. Aemond.

123
00:12:28.665 --> 00:12:30.792
I have found myself
of little use here of late.

124
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:36.589
And what of Harrenhal?

125
00:12:37.632 --> 00:12:39.842
You and Vhagar were meant to fly
to meet Ser Criston

126
00:12:39.926 --> 00:12:41.469
and challenge Daemon together.

127
00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:46.808
Aegon has left me no choice
but to remain here and defend the city.

128
00:12:49.686 --> 00:12:52.188
But aid is coming.

129
00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:54.524
Lord Ormund and 15.000 Hightower men

130
00:12:54.607 --> 00:12:56.985
presently march up the Mander
with Daeron and his dragon.

131
00:12:57.068 --> 00:12:59.362
And the Triarchy fleet will.
at any moment.

132
00:12:59.445 --> 00:13:02.657
ambush the blockade with a force
thrice the Sea Snake's strength.

133
00:13:07.954 --> 00:13:09.580
We only need to bide our time.

134
00:14:45.551 --> 00:14:47.303
The Lannister host has scattered.
my prince.

135
00:14:47.387 --> 00:14:50.390
The vanguard was smashed
and the rearguard broken and fled.

136
00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:56.270
And what of the golden Lord Lannister?

137
00:14:57.313 --> 00:14:59.148
Fled when the cavalry broke rank.

138
00:14:59.232 --> 00:15:01.859
Our scouts believe they may be
regrouping near the God's Eye.

139
00:15:01.943 --> 00:15:03.383
Then we'll continue the fight there.

140
00:15:03.444 --> 00:15:05.279
We must pursue them till the last.

141
00:15:05.363 --> 00:15:08.616
- Have graves dug for our dead.
- Aye. my lord.

142
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:10.701
Caraxes would make short work
of these bodies.

143
00:15:11.577 --> 00:15:13.871
And burnt flesh carries no plague.

144
00:15:13.955 --> 00:15:15.915
That is not our way.

145
00:15:15.998 --> 00:15:17.875
Rivermen must be returned to the mud.

146
00:15:21.421 --> 00:15:22.547
My lord!

147
00:15:29.595 --> 00:15:30.595
To arms!

148
00:15:31.556 --> 00:15:32.557
Form on me!

149
00:16:43.377 --> 00:16:47.590
We have come to die for the dragon queen.

150
00:16:57.725 --> 00:17:01.062
Very good. We've got more lions to hunt.

151
00:17:55.825 --> 00:17:57.410
Good morrow. Lord Hand.

152
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:02.306
Has there been word from Prince Aemond?

153
00:18:03.332 --> 00:18:05.459
None. As yet.

154
00:18:07.545 --> 00:18:09.064
He and Vhagar were
supposed to have joined us

155
00:18:09.088 --> 00:18:10.423
back at the Antlers.

156
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:14.468
We march ever exposed.

157
00:18:14.552 --> 00:18:16.387
- If he does not come...
- He has to come.

158
00:18:21.309 --> 00:18:22.727
There is another matter.

159
00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:25.980
One of our men has ravaged a village girl.

160
00:18:26.981 --> 00:18:28.316
I witnessed the events myself.

161
00:18:29.900 --> 00:18:31.319
Something must be done.

162
00:18:32.528 --> 00:18:34.739
Hang him then. if you wish.

163
00:18:35.865 --> 00:18:38.075
I am not his Lord Commander.

164
00:18:41.245 --> 00:18:46.334
A punishment is due. yes.
but also a statement to the men.

165
00:18:47.209 --> 00:18:49.712
That we are not beasts. but knights.

166
00:18:49.795 --> 00:18:51.213
and soldiers of honor.

167
00:18:51.297 --> 00:18:52.882
Look around you. Ser Gwayne.

168
00:18:56.052 --> 00:18:59.221
Look to the sky. To the horizon.

169
00:19:00.765 --> 00:19:02.433
Doom and ruin surround us.

170
00:19:05.269 --> 00:19:07.438
We will all become beasts before our end.

171
00:19:08.314 --> 00:19:10.232
Only if we abandon our principles.

172
00:19:18.783 --> 00:19:20.409
Never knew my mother.

173
00:19:23.079 --> 00:19:25.456
Same as most of the gutter-rats.

174
00:19:30.169 --> 00:19:32.880
Was kicked about more than a mongrel dog.

175
00:19:39.136 --> 00:19:41.597
Wished for death more days
than I wished to live.

176
00:19:47.603 --> 00:19:50.398
There was this priest from Essos.

177
00:19:52.525 --> 00:19:55.778
He fancied me. Paid me coin.

178
00:20:00.449 --> 00:20:01.575
To do things.

179
00:20:06.497 --> 00:20:08.457
He said I had king's blood.

180
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:10.960
That I was born for a purpose.

181
00:20:13.546 --> 00:20:14.922
I liked that story.

182
00:20:16.632 --> 00:20:17.883
So I owned it.

183
00:20:20.094 --> 00:20:21.762
Ulf the Dragonseed.

184
00:20:26.934 --> 00:20:28.936
And that red cunt was right.

185
00:20:33.190 --> 00:20:34.525
And you?

186
00:20:34.608 --> 00:20:36.694
Where'd you get your dragon's blood?

187
00:20:43.284 --> 00:20:44.535
Did you hear something?

188
00:20:47.872 --> 00:20:49.582
Don't like this place.

189
00:20:49.665 --> 00:20:51.709
All this hanging about.

190
00:20:51.792 --> 00:20:53.544
Vhagar was supposed to be here already.

191
00:20:53.627 --> 00:20:55.129
We have to wait until she comes.

192
00:20:55.212 --> 00:20:57.089
The queen didn't say
nothing about waiting.

193
00:20:57.173 --> 00:20:59.425
She said. come here. kill Aemond.

194
00:20:59.508 --> 00:21:01.594
I wouldn't be too keen to meet Vhagar.

195
00:21:02.303 --> 00:21:04.614
She and the One-Eye have slain
at least two dragons already.

196
00:21:04.638 --> 00:21:06.348
Fight'll be worth it. though.

197
00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:08.768
For the castle.

198
00:21:09.852 --> 00:21:10.853
What castle?

199
00:21:11.771 --> 00:21:14.774
The queen promised to make us knights.

200
00:21:14.857 --> 00:21:16.692
so we get a castle.

201
00:21:24.617 --> 00:21:26.911
- What?
- You have to be named a lord

202
00:21:26.994 --> 00:21:28.078
to get a castle.

203
00:21:28.162 --> 00:21:29.747
- What's a knight get. then?
- A horse.

204
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:31.749
What do I need with a fucking horse?

205
00:21:31.832 --> 00:21:34.460
- I've got a dragon.
- You'd be Ser Ulf.

206
00:21:34.543 --> 00:21:36.337
and men would have to show you respect.

207
00:21:36.420 --> 00:21:40.382
Men would have to show me respect
'cause of the big fucking dragon.

208
00:21:42.384 --> 00:21:43.761
I can't live in a title.

209
00:21:44.637 --> 00:21:45.805
Or drink it.

210
00:21:50.476 --> 00:21:52.269
I imagine there'd be eager women.

211
00:21:54.396 --> 00:21:56.273
Get more women with a castle.

212
00:23:02.131 --> 00:23:04.592
Did you know Aegon had fled?

213
00:23:08.929 --> 00:23:10.097
He was meant to be here.

214
00:23:11.557 --> 00:23:13.517
It's Aemond who should have flown.

215
00:23:14.810 --> 00:23:15.936
You're frightened.

216
00:23:19.732 --> 00:23:22.151
Ser Criston and Ser Gwayne
are in great peril.

217
00:23:23.277 --> 00:23:24.904
I fear only for our knights.

218
00:23:26.989 --> 00:23:28.282
Aemond should be with them.

219
00:23:28.365 --> 00:23:30.075
Aemond's frightened. too.

220
00:23:32.244 --> 00:23:35.748
After he claimed Vhagar.
he forgot what fear was.

221
00:23:36.832 --> 00:23:38.250
But he remembers now.

222
00:23:39.585 --> 00:23:42.755
He knows that if he has to face
Rhaenyra's dragons. he'll die.

223
00:23:52.264 --> 00:23:53.641
Ser Soren?

224
00:23:58.771 --> 00:24:01.649
Lord Ormund marches here
with the Hightower host.

225
00:24:01.732 --> 00:24:04.985
Dispatch one of your fastest riders
and deliver this to him with haste.

226
00:24:05.861 --> 00:24:07.221
These are the king's instructions.

227
00:24:07.279 --> 00:24:08.405
The king's?

228
00:24:10.324 --> 00:24:12.701
- With haste. Ser Soren.
- At once. Your Grace.

229
00:24:16.288 --> 00:24:17.665
Alyn. sit.

230
00:24:37.267 --> 00:24:38.602
I saved this one.

231
00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:42.147
It's from Ib.

232
00:24:43.315 --> 00:24:45.275
Such luxury is wasted on me.

233
00:24:47.653 --> 00:24:49.279
I've already broken the wax.

234
00:24:52.116 --> 00:24:54.118
And I am not prepared...

235
00:24:57.121 --> 00:24:58.580
to drink alone.

236
00:25:15.514 --> 00:25:18.475
I forget the guttural name
they have for it.

237
00:25:20.019 --> 00:25:22.813
But I believe a rough interpretation
is "dragon water."

238
00:25:25.399 --> 00:25:27.401
An acquired taste. perhaps.

239
00:25:29.445 --> 00:25:30.779
The queen has sent word.

240
00:25:32.281 --> 00:25:34.033
We are to pull five ships
from the blockade.

241
00:25:34.116 --> 00:25:36.952
sail down the Blackwater.
and seize King's Landing's port.

242
00:25:37.036 --> 00:25:38.787
She's taking King's Landing?

243
00:25:38.871 --> 00:25:40.706
Rhaenyra's advantage is now absolute.

244
00:25:40.789 --> 00:25:43.667
She will surround the city
with her dragons

245
00:25:43.751 --> 00:25:45.961
and force the surrender
of Aegon and Aemond.

246
00:25:47.337 --> 00:25:49.465
I admit I know little of this enemy.

247
00:25:50.799 --> 00:25:52.301
But Aemond One-Eye seems the sort

248
00:25:52.384 --> 00:25:54.803
who would sooner let it all burn
than abandon the throne.

249
00:25:57.264 --> 00:25:58.849
Rough seas lie ahead.

250
00:26:12.362 --> 00:26:15.407
I cannot fully mend...

251
00:26:16.658 --> 00:26:20.829
the breach between us.

252
00:26:22.331 --> 00:26:24.541
But I do accept that it was of my making.

253
00:26:29.797 --> 00:26:31.131
I was fond of your mother.

254
00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:34.301
For...

255
00:26:35.469 --> 00:26:36.970
whatever we had together.

256
00:26:41.391 --> 00:26:43.435
I did try to provide a life for you.

257
00:26:45.104 --> 00:26:48.482
- For your brother.
- A life. perhaps.

258
00:26:48.565 --> 00:26:50.025
But never a name.

259
00:26:58.450 --> 00:27:00.035
I am sorry for it.

260
00:27:01.870 --> 00:27:03.413
Sail ho!

261
00:27:24.143 --> 00:27:26.395
Enemy ships sighted!

262
00:27:33.402 --> 00:27:35.737
- Enemy ships sighted.
- What is their strength?

263
00:27:35.821 --> 00:27:37.322
Three-and-fifty counted so far.

264
00:27:37.406 --> 00:27:38.615
They already outnumber us.

265
00:27:40.242 --> 00:27:43.370
Put the oars out.
Send ravens to Dragonstone.

266
00:27:43.453 --> 00:27:45.038
Put the oars out!

267
00:27:45.122 --> 00:27:48.917
Take us to the head of the blockade
and signal the fleet: Form battle lines.

268
00:27:49.001 --> 00:27:50.878
Is it the Lannisters or the Greyjoys?

269
00:27:51.962 --> 00:27:53.255
It's the Triarchy.

270
00:27:55.757 --> 00:27:57.509
Bring my armor.

271
00:28:20.199 --> 00:28:21.200
Commander.

272
00:28:23.577 --> 00:28:25.913
The Gullet has three inlets
into the Blackwater.

273
00:28:25.996 --> 00:28:29.791
the largest of which opens
just to the south of Driftmark.

274
00:28:29.875 --> 00:28:33.253
But I hold strongly that we must press
towards the southern inlet.

275
00:28:33.337 --> 00:28:36.798
If our armada engages the Velaryon fleet
at close combat.

276
00:28:36.882 --> 00:28:38.967
it will blunt the threat
of Rhaenyra's dragons.

277
00:28:39.051 --> 00:28:41.345
They will be loath
to burn their own ships.

278
00:28:41.428 --> 00:28:43.013
A canny strategy. my lord.

279
00:28:44.056 --> 00:28:46.642
I can see why your king
made you Lord of the Ships.

280
00:28:49.770 --> 00:28:52.439
You'll rule all this kit
if you wind up in the drink.

281
00:28:54.316 --> 00:28:57.736
My strategy is expressly
not to "end up in the drink."

282
00:29:00.489 --> 00:29:03.450
We will face death on this deck
before we face it in the sea.

283
00:29:04.284 --> 00:29:06.495
You will be glad of our armor
when the fighting starts.

284
00:29:06.578 --> 00:29:08.038
I know I will.

285
00:29:08.121 --> 00:29:11.124
The Sea Snake scouts have
raised the alarm. Commander.

286
00:29:12.417 --> 00:29:14.253
If only to see his face.

287
00:29:15.712 --> 00:29:17.589
Signal Halfjaw to take his detachment

288
00:29:17.673 --> 00:29:19.258
and penetrate the northern pass.

289
00:29:19.341 --> 00:29:20.968
The northern pass

290
00:29:21.051 --> 00:29:22.302
is the farthest route

291
00:29:22.386 --> 00:29:24.066
running north of Dragonstone.
Whatever for?

292
00:29:25.097 --> 00:29:26.348
To sack High Tide.

293
00:29:27.724 --> 00:29:29.101
Lord Corlys' castle?

294
00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:32.771
We will require
the full strength of your fleet

295
00:29:32.854 --> 00:29:34.749
- if we have any hope...
- High Tide is a monument

296
00:29:34.773 --> 00:29:36.275
to the Sea Snake himself.

297
00:29:38.735 --> 00:29:42.322
Do you think his focus will hold
when he sees his treasure room aflame?

298
00:31:05.364 --> 00:31:07.991
What is the weather to be today. Bold Jon?

299
00:31:08.075 --> 00:31:10.535
Raining piss or shit.
from the looks of the messenger.

300
00:31:13.080 --> 00:31:16.208
Good morrow. ser. What news?

301
00:31:16.291 --> 00:31:17.876
Good morrow. my Lord Hightower.

302
00:31:20.379 --> 00:31:21.922
I bring urgent word from King Aemond.

303
00:31:22.798 --> 00:31:24.049
King. is he now?

304
00:31:54.996 --> 00:31:58.291
Aemond says we have to make camp here
and await further word.

305
00:31:59.292 --> 00:32:01.128
He shall join us in three days' time.

306
00:32:07.634 --> 00:32:09.219
So Aegon's dead. then?

307
00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:15.559
One king is as good as another.

308
00:32:16.476 --> 00:32:18.895
Have this lad bathed and fed.

309
00:32:18.979 --> 00:32:20.856
- Give him a good tent.
- Yes. sire.

310
00:32:25.402 --> 00:32:27.863
Mayhaps the weather will hold.

311
00:32:33.577 --> 00:32:36.037
It is my fault we're in this position.

312
00:32:46.840 --> 00:32:50.051
I strove tirelessly to put Aegon
on the throne. but I...

313
00:32:52.345 --> 00:32:54.264
I failed to prepare him to rule.

314
00:32:58.977 --> 00:33:00.854
His frailties are his own.

315
00:33:06.818 --> 00:33:08.403
You should have been king.

316
00:33:12.574 --> 00:33:14.576
If you'd only been born first.
then perhaps

317
00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:16.536
we wouldn't be here. but...

318
00:33:18.497 --> 00:33:20.582
we must ever play the board before us.

319
00:33:31.051 --> 00:33:35.555
That is why you need to go to Harrenhal.

320
00:33:40.685 --> 00:33:41.770
To what end?

321
00:33:41.853 --> 00:33:43.605
It is a stronghold.

322
00:33:44.898 --> 00:33:47.526
One that has withstood
dragon fire once before.

323
00:33:47.609 --> 00:33:50.362
You are no longer safe here
in King's Landing.

324
00:33:58.495 --> 00:34:00.830
It is well to be fearful.

325
00:34:00.914 --> 00:34:02.415
I. too. am afraid.

326
00:34:05.752 --> 00:34:07.379
I'm not afraid.

327
00:34:14.803 --> 00:34:16.012
Of course not.

328
00:34:16.846 --> 00:34:18.223
But you are the crown now.

329
00:34:20.141 --> 00:34:22.686
And Rhaenyra will send
her new dragons here for you.

330
00:34:23.812 --> 00:34:25.021
Soon or late.

331
00:34:28.608 --> 00:34:30.235
I am not afraid.

332
00:34:35.991 --> 00:34:37.409
Fly to the Riverlands.

333
00:34:37.492 --> 00:34:39.202
Draw Daemon out.

334
00:34:40.203 --> 00:34:43.540
He has just one dragon. and killing him
would be a vicious blow to Rhaenyra.

335
00:34:45.708 --> 00:34:48.587
At Harrenhal. you will be unassailable.

336
00:34:53.049 --> 00:34:54.592
Perhaps I could even meet you there.

337
00:34:57.721 --> 00:34:59.264
That road is uncertain.

338
00:35:01.182 --> 00:35:02.726
But this one.

339
00:35:02.809 --> 00:35:04.811
if you stay here and wait for Rhaenyra

340
00:35:04.894 --> 00:35:08.106
and her dragons to come.
this one is certain.

341
00:35:12.819 --> 00:35:14.404
You are so courageous.

342
00:35:16.865 --> 00:35:18.867
But I cannot lose you as I did Aegon.

343
00:35:21.369 --> 00:35:23.038
If I do. I will be lost.

344
00:35:26.291 --> 00:35:28.627
Heed me. Aemond. please.

345
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:09.542
I shall host a feast there in your honor.

346
00:36:10.752 --> 00:36:12.379
In Black Harren's hall

347
00:36:13.880 --> 00:36:16.174
whilst my uncle's head
looks down from a spike.

348
00:36:44.536 --> 00:36:45.536
Fuck!

349
00:36:47.580 --> 00:36:50.291
What if Aemond
knew we were coming for him?

350
00:36:51.334 --> 00:36:53.420
He could have attacked
Dragonstone in our absence.

351
00:36:54.546 --> 00:36:57.674
Queen assigned us a task.
We must man it steadfastly.

352
00:36:58.800 --> 00:37:01.136
And if that is what the enemy
is counting upon?

353
00:37:11.896 --> 00:37:13.773
- What is that?
- Fuck this place!

354
00:37:13.857 --> 00:37:16.526
- What's happened?
- I'm leaving is what's happened.

355
00:37:16.609 --> 00:37:18.111
We must wait for Vhagar.

356
00:37:18.194 --> 00:37:20.739
For how long? Forever and a day?

357
00:37:20.822 --> 00:37:22.240
She was meant to be here already.

358
00:37:24.367 --> 00:37:26.244
The queen only instructed us
to ambush Vhagar.

359
00:37:26.327 --> 00:37:28.055
She did not say what to do
if the dragon never came.

360
00:37:28.079 --> 00:37:29.581
I say we remain.

361
00:37:29.664 --> 00:37:31.207
Who made you fucking king?

362
00:37:31.833 --> 00:37:32.834
I don't like it here.

363
00:37:32.917 --> 00:37:34.502
Is that what you'll tell Her Grace?

364
00:37:34.586 --> 00:37:37.255
- That you're craven?
- I'll tell Her Grace true.

365
00:37:37.338 --> 00:37:40.592
That we stood watch and Vhagar never came.

366
00:37:40.675 --> 00:37:42.510
Your friend's right.

367
00:37:46.848 --> 00:37:48.641
You're missing the battle.

368
00:37:48.725 --> 00:37:50.560
The queen needs you at Dragonstone.

369
00:37:53.396 --> 00:37:54.397
Who are you?

370
00:37:55.482 --> 00:37:56.566
I'm a witch.

371
00:38:01.821 --> 00:38:03.448
Right. Look after yourselves.

372
00:38:19.547 --> 00:38:20.840
Your Grace!

373
00:38:21.382 --> 00:38:24.260
- There is war in the Gullet.
- Who?

374
00:38:24.344 --> 00:38:25.553
An armada of ships

375
00:38:25.637 --> 00:38:27.680
sailing out of the rising sun
from the east.

376
00:38:27.764 --> 00:38:29.307
They have sprung their trap.

377
00:38:34.896 --> 00:38:35.939
I shall go.

378
00:38:44.113 --> 00:38:45.240
Mother!

379
00:38:45.949 --> 00:38:47.617
Stop! You cannot!

380
00:38:47.700 --> 00:38:50.328
There is nothing you can say
that I have not heard.

381
00:38:50.411 --> 00:38:51.496
If you die...

382
00:38:52.497 --> 00:38:53.915
Then you will at last be king.

383
00:38:56.334 --> 00:38:57.836
My riding leathers.

384
00:39:06.261 --> 00:39:08.805
You are to lock and bar this door.

385
00:39:09.722 --> 00:39:12.475
The queen must be confined
until she regains her senses.

386
00:39:12.559 --> 00:39:14.561
I could not defy Her Grace's commands.

387
00:39:14.644 --> 00:39:18.022
You are a knight of the Queensguard.
Ser Lorent.

388
00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:22.110
You swore to protect
Her Grace from all threats.

389
00:39:23.528 --> 00:39:25.071
Including herself.

390
00:39:30.827 --> 00:39:31.995
Your life...

391
00:39:33.246 --> 00:39:34.330
for hers.

392
00:39:43.256 --> 00:39:44.674
Jace.

393
00:39:44.757 --> 00:39:46.134
Rescind your command.

394
00:39:46.217 --> 00:39:48.469
- It is treason.
- She has rejected my counsel.

395
00:39:48.553 --> 00:39:50.013
my every attempt to join the fight.

396
00:39:50.096 --> 00:39:52.432
So you make war with her instead?

397
00:39:52.515 --> 00:39:54.893
This is all the work of an ambush.
like Rook's Rest.

398
00:39:54.976 --> 00:39:57.186
a ruse to draw out the queen herself.

399
00:39:57.270 --> 00:40:00.148
They killed my brother. Baela.

400
00:40:01.149 --> 00:40:02.775
I won't let them take her as well.

401
00:40:10.450 --> 00:40:11.826
Come with me.

402
00:40:13.703 --> 00:40:15.496
We are ready.

403
00:40:17.123 --> 00:40:18.666
We can win this victory for her.

404
00:40:20.251 --> 00:40:22.670
Was this not always our purpose?

405
00:40:47.612 --> 00:40:49.906
Ser Lorent. open the door.

406
00:40:49.989 --> 00:40:52.533
Your Grace.
it was the Prince Jacaerys' command.

407
00:40:53.743 --> 00:40:55.036
To ensure your safety.

408
00:40:55.119 --> 00:40:57.163
Open the fucking door.

409
00:40:57.246 --> 00:40:58.246
I cannot.

410
00:40:59.332 --> 00:41:00.875
Ser Lorent!

411
00:41:02.585 --> 00:41:04.087
Jace!

412
00:41:07.006 --> 00:41:08.800
You open the fucking door!

413
00:41:10.385 --> 00:41:12.095
You release me at once!

414
00:41:12.178 --> 00:41:14.389
I will have your heads for this!

415
00:41:42.917 --> 00:41:45.336
Crossbows. ready!

416
00:41:45.420 --> 00:41:46.838
Release!

417
00:41:46.921 --> 00:41:49.340
Archers. ready!

418
00:41:50.466 --> 00:41:51.551
Release!

419
00:41:52.260 --> 00:41:54.429
Archers. ready!

420
00:41:54.512 --> 00:41:55.972
Release!

421
00:41:56.055 --> 00:41:58.474
Barrelman! Signal the fleet:

422
00:41:58.558 --> 00:42:00.184
Do not cluster.

423
00:42:00.268 --> 00:42:01.561
Keep them on the chase.

424
00:42:01.644 --> 00:42:03.521
- Aye-aye!
- The fight is yours.

425
00:42:03.604 --> 00:42:05.148
Archers. ready!

426
00:42:05.231 --> 00:42:07.191
Archers. go!

427
00:42:07.275 --> 00:42:08.276
Loose!

428
00:42:08.359 --> 00:42:10.028
Flagship's been sighted. m'lord.

429
00:42:11.070 --> 00:42:12.238
It's the Bitchfist.

430
00:42:12.321 --> 00:42:13.322
Lohar?

431
00:42:16.617 --> 00:42:18.870
Harden up and make towards her.

432
00:42:18.953 --> 00:42:21.372
- I want her to sight us.
- Aye. m'lord.

433
00:42:22.290 --> 00:42:23.583
Harden up! Pick up the stroke!

434
00:42:51.319 --> 00:42:52.779
Here she comes. lads!

435
00:42:52.862 --> 00:42:55.031
Our jewel in the rough.

436
00:42:55.114 --> 00:42:59.035
Signal the fleet.
The Sea Snake belongs to us.

437
00:42:59.118 --> 00:43:02.121
An equal share of the plunder
when we take the ship!

438
00:43:02.205 --> 00:43:03.748
- Aye. Commander!
- Commander!

439
00:43:04.916 --> 00:43:06.417
Commander!

440
00:43:06.501 --> 00:43:08.211
Ours is the flagship.

441
00:43:08.294 --> 00:43:10.546
We cannot give ourselves
to a singular pursuit.

442
00:43:10.630 --> 00:43:13.049
We must lead the assault
lest it fall into disorder.

443
00:43:14.509 --> 00:43:16.260
Do you think I sailed
across the Narrow Sea

444
00:43:16.344 --> 00:43:18.179
to win your king's war for him?

445
00:43:19.847 --> 00:43:22.183
Those were the terms of the contract.

446
00:43:23.434 --> 00:43:25.603
The Sea Snake led
the persecution and slaughter

447
00:43:25.686 --> 00:43:27.814
of my mates for more than 20 years.

448
00:43:29.065 --> 00:43:30.650
I sealed your contract for him.

449
00:43:32.360 --> 00:43:36.030
Tonight. we shall walk
in the ashes of High Tide!

450
00:43:36.114 --> 00:43:39.200
You'll all join me as I sit
the Driftwood Throne

451
00:43:39.283 --> 00:43:41.369
and dine on the Sea Snake's ears!

452
00:43:43.996 --> 00:43:45.164
Break us free!

453
00:43:46.958 --> 00:43:48.292
And give chase!

454
00:44:02.890 --> 00:44:04.892
He wishes only to protect you.

455
00:44:04.976 --> 00:44:06.727
I never asked to be protected.

456
00:44:18.406 --> 00:44:20.158
I expect it from my council.

457
00:44:20.241 --> 00:44:23.536
those craven men ever clutching
at their doublets.

458
00:44:23.619 --> 00:44:24.954
But my Queensguard?

459
00:44:25.037 --> 00:44:26.497
Mine own son?

460
00:45:19.842 --> 00:45:22.136
I may appear to have the weak
and feeble body of a woman.

461
00:45:22.220 --> 00:45:24.472
but I possess the heart
and spirit of a king.

462
00:45:28.267 --> 00:45:30.269
Enemy to starboard!

463
00:45:30.353 --> 00:45:32.271
- Split. split. split!
- Ballistae. reload!

464
00:45:32.355 --> 00:45:33.856
And put those fires out!

465
00:45:36.359 --> 00:45:37.944
The fleet is surrounded.

466
00:45:38.027 --> 00:45:40.267
And the Bitchfist now pursues us
with a small detachment.

467
00:45:41.072 --> 00:45:42.907
- Dragon!
- Dragon!

468
00:45:50.539 --> 00:45:52.124
Dracarys!

469
00:45:56.212 --> 00:45:57.421
Dracarys!

470
00:46:13.729 --> 00:46:15.856
Set a course through the Dragonstone Pass.

471
00:46:17.858 --> 00:46:20.152
The tide is nearly out. We'll run aground.

472
00:46:21.529 --> 00:46:24.532
Lohar only wants me. She'll follow.

473
00:46:25.658 --> 00:46:27.868
Without her.
their fleet will be rudderless...

474
00:46:28.995 --> 00:46:30.705
and easy prey for our dragons.

475
00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:35.835
Starboard on our helm!

476
00:46:35.918 --> 00:46:37.670
Fight ready. men!

477
00:46:37.753 --> 00:46:39.630
Bring the grapnels!

478
00:46:46.679 --> 00:46:48.222
- Ready?
- Ready!

479
00:46:53.269 --> 00:46:54.270
Load!

480
00:47:25.343 --> 00:47:28.262
Call me Lohar. Dragon-Slayer!

481
00:47:28.971 --> 00:47:30.348
Press the pursuit!

482
00:48:33.494 --> 00:48:36.038
Ease the sheets and put out the oars.

483
00:48:36.122 --> 00:48:38.040
Cast the lead lines.

484
00:48:38.124 --> 00:48:40.042
Clew up the course.

485
00:48:40.126 --> 00:48:42.378
Leadsmen. to the channels.

486
00:48:42.461 --> 00:48:44.004
Cast the lead line!

487
00:48:57.852 --> 00:49:00.521
Depth. six fathoms!

488
00:49:00.604 --> 00:49:02.314
Barrelman. report!

489
00:49:02.398 --> 00:49:04.984
Breakers dead ahead.

490
00:49:05.067 --> 00:49:06.986
Tide's running hard out.

491
00:49:07.069 --> 00:49:09.447
Currents are strong set to larboard.

492
00:49:14.034 --> 00:49:17.830
Three enemy ships closing fast astern!

493
00:49:18.664 --> 00:49:19.957
Larboard your helm.

494
00:49:21.792 --> 00:49:23.210
Follow my direction closely.

495
00:49:23.294 --> 00:49:26.130
There is a way through the pass.
but it is narrow.

496
00:49:27.256 --> 00:49:30.217
Half-five and fast receding!

497
00:49:32.553 --> 00:49:34.680
- Seven!
- Seven knots!

498
00:49:34.763 --> 00:49:36.474
Slight to larboard.

499
00:49:36.557 --> 00:49:37.933
Aye. Lord Admiral.

500
00:49:38.934 --> 00:49:42.021
- Follow her wake.
- We must go no further.

501
00:49:42.104 --> 00:49:43.814
The pass is too shallow.

502
00:49:45.441 --> 00:49:47.443
We do not know the lay of this place.

503
00:49:48.777 --> 00:49:51.280
- We are sailing blind.
- The Sea Snake will guide us.

504
00:49:58.120 --> 00:50:00.831
- One over four!
- One over four!

505
00:50:00.915 --> 00:50:03.667
Perhaps 70 yards' distance.

506
00:50:03.751 --> 00:50:04.751
Easy now.

507
00:50:05.461 --> 00:50:06.754
Starboard your helm.

508
00:50:10.508 --> 00:50:11.342
Too strong.

509
00:50:11.425 --> 00:50:12.551
Ease it back.

510
00:50:19.808 --> 00:50:20.893
Let me.

511
00:50:22.728 --> 00:50:24.313
Forty yards now.

512
00:50:25.523 --> 00:50:26.607
Thirty-five!

513
00:50:27.691 --> 00:50:30.444
- And a half-three!
- And a half-three!

514
00:50:30.528 --> 00:50:32.279
Bank the oars.

515
00:50:32.363 --> 00:50:34.698
Coxswain ahoy! Bank oars!

516
00:50:40.829 --> 00:50:44.208
- Twenty-five yards!
- Twenty-five yards!

517
00:50:44.291 --> 00:50:46.502
- One over three!
- Ten yards!

518
00:50:46.585 --> 00:50:48.963
- Ten yards!
- We're over the Teeth!

519
00:51:11.235 --> 00:51:12.528
We're clear!

520
00:51:21.120 --> 00:51:23.372
Leave Lohar to the Teeth.

521
00:51:23.455 --> 00:51:26.333
Take us back to the Gullet.
We must rejoin the fight.

522
00:52:04.038 --> 00:52:06.206
Three hands to starboard. now!

523
00:52:06.290 --> 00:52:09.043
- Three hands to starboard!
- We're going to wreck!

524
00:52:16.216 --> 00:52:19.511
We have walked directly into his snare.

525
00:52:19.595 --> 00:52:21.847
Two hands to larboard now
and hold her there!

526
00:52:21.930 --> 00:52:24.516
- Two hands to larboard. hold!
- Cut the anchors!

527
00:52:24.600 --> 00:52:27.144
Drop weight and raise our draft. Quickly!

528
00:52:27.227 --> 00:52:29.563
Aye. Commander! Cut the anchors!

529
00:52:34.902 --> 00:52:36.612
What do you weigh in that armor?

530
00:52:40.407 --> 00:52:42.117
And the rest of them!

531
00:52:42.201 --> 00:52:45.704
Hold that line.
and pull the fucking oars in!

532
00:53:04.056 --> 00:53:07.309
Oars out and close the distance!
Bring the hooks and lines!

533
00:53:07.393 --> 00:53:10.062
Enemy flagship is clear.

534
00:53:10.145 --> 00:53:12.064
She's closing fast astern.

535
00:53:13.315 --> 00:53:15.693
She has the legs on us.
We can't outrun her.

536
00:53:15.776 --> 00:53:18.096
And we've not yet the wind
to carry us against the current.

537
00:53:19.488 --> 00:53:21.573
Furl the sails and put the oars out.

538
00:53:21.657 --> 00:53:23.033
Hard round to starboard.

539
00:53:23.117 --> 00:53:25.285
Ready the offensive
for a broadside assault.

540
00:53:25.369 --> 00:53:28.038
All shields and crossbows.
to your stations!

541
00:53:28.122 --> 00:53:29.748
Load the ballistae!

542
00:53:38.757 --> 00:53:41.635
- Boarding party!
- Boarding party.

543
00:53:44.930 --> 00:53:48.475
Hard about and keep pulling!
Strong against the current.

544
00:53:48.559 --> 00:53:50.602
- Turn!
- Or she'll be dragged back into the Teeth.

545
00:54:05.159 --> 00:54:06.660
She's not turning!

546
00:54:11.081 --> 00:54:12.875
All shields and crossbows to starboard!

547
00:54:14.626 --> 00:54:16.211
Broadside. ready!

548
00:54:19.798 --> 00:54:22.551
Positions. move! Positions!

549
00:54:31.477 --> 00:54:33.937
- Crossbows. ready!
- Ready!

550
00:54:34.021 --> 00:54:35.022
Strike!

551
00:54:39.067 --> 00:54:42.029
Hold that course and fucking row!

552
00:54:45.032 --> 00:54:47.367
Brace and be ready!

553
00:54:47.451 --> 00:54:48.744
Now. strike!

554
00:55:02.049 --> 00:55:03.383
Take the ship.

555
00:55:06.428 --> 00:55:08.889
On your feet! Prepare to engage!

556
00:55:30.327 --> 00:55:31.745
Dracarys!

557
00:55:40.546 --> 00:55:42.214
Bring down the rider!

558
00:58:19.788 --> 00:58:22.040
No! No!

559
00:58:22.124 --> 00:58:24.126
Sheep stealer. no!

560
00:58:28.296 --> 00:58:29.923
That's my sister.

561
00:59:47.959 --> 00:59:48.960
Father!

562
01:00:05.477 --> 01:00:06.561
Hold on. Baela!

563
01:00:13.443 --> 01:00:14.444
Rhaena!

564
01:00:22.869 --> 01:00:24.371
Sheep stealer!

565
01:00:38.343 --> 01:00:40.720
Sheep stealer! No!

566
01:00:46.143 --> 01:00:47.144
Vermax!

567
01:01:00.532 --> 01:01:01.825
Jace!

568
01:02:07.724 --> 01:02:09.559
Jace!

569
01:02:17.442 --> 01:02:18.860
Come on. Vermax!

570
01:02:19.305 --> 01:03:19.714
